#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.229"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.229:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.229:0.2"
msgid "23. Dīghacārikavagga"
msgstr "23. Long Wandering"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.229:0.3"
msgid "229. Paṭhamakaṇhasappasutta"
msgstr "229. Black Snakes (1st)"

# Note that here once again it is clear adinava does not mean “danger”. Only one of the five factors is actually the dangerous nature of the snake.
#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.229:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā kaṇhasappe."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks of a black snake."

msgctxt "an5.229:1.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

# I’m not sure why BB has “frightening “for sabhiru. The dicts give “fearful”, see opp. abhiru in CPD.” frightening, dangerous” seems to be redundant, while “cowardly” is not. Also, below a charnel ground is said to be sappatibbhaya. It’s not so obvious that a charnel ground is “dangerous”, but it certainly is “frightening”.
msgctxt "an5.229:1.3"
msgid "Asuci, duggandho, sabhīru, sappaṭibhayo, mittadubbhī."
msgstr "It’s filthy, stinking, cowardly, frightening, and treacherous."

msgctxt "an5.229:1.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā kaṇhasappe."
msgstr "These are the five dangers of a black snake."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.229:2.1"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcime ādīnavā mātugāme."
msgstr "In the same way there are five drawbacks of a female."

msgctxt "an5.229:2.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.229:2.3"
msgid "Asuci, duggandho, sabhīru, sappaṭibhayo, mittadubbhī."
msgstr "She’s filthy, stinking, cowardly, frightening, and treacherous."

msgctxt "an5.229:2.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā mātugāme”ti."
msgstr "These are the five drawbacks of a female.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.229:2.5"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
